   "source": [
    "# Calculating NDVI"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyrasterframes import *\n",
    "from pyrasterframes.rasterfunctions import *\n",
    "from pyspark.sql import *\n",
    "from pyspark.sql.functions import udf\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.image as mpimg\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "spark = SparkSession.builder. \\\n",
    "    master(\"local[*]\"). \\\n",
    "    appName(\"RasterFrames\"). \\\n",
    "    config(\"spark.ui.enabled\", \"false\"). \\\n",
    "    getOrCreate(). \\\n",
    "    withRasterFrames()\n",
    "    \n",
    "resource_dir = Path('./samples').resolve()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "redBand = spark.read.geotiff(resource_dir.joinpath('L8-B4-Elkton-VA.tiff').as_uri()).withColumnRenamed('tile', 'red_band')\n",
    "nirBand = spark.read.geotiff(resource_dir.joinpath('L8-B5-Elkton-VA.tiff').as_uri()).withColumnRenamed('tile', 'nir_band')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "|tileStats(ndvi)                                                                        |\n",
      "+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "|[28561,-0.10896296054124832,0.669983446598053,0.45550015129027654,0.010856412948156034]|\n",
      "+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# shouldn't those values be switched? Why is the mean of the normalized difference above 1?\n",
    "rf = redBand.asRF().spatialJoin(nirBand.asRF()) \\\n",
    "    .withColumn(\"ndvi\", normalizedDifference(convertCellType('nir_band', 'float32'), convertCellType('red_band', 'float32'))).asRF()\n",
    "rf.select(tileStats('ndvi')).show(1, False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "+------------------------+\n",
      "|celltypeexpression(ndvi)|\n",
      "+------------------------+\n",
      "|                 float32|\n",
      "+------------------------+\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rf.select(cellType('ndvi')).show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pixels = np.reshape(np.asarray(rf.select(tileToDoubleArray('ndvi')).first()), (-1, 169))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rfpixels = rf.toDoubleRaster('ndvi', 169, 169)"
   ]
  },
